Movistar Logo Movistar is a major telecommunications brand owned by Telefónica, operating in Spain and in many Latin American countries. It is the largest mobile phone operator in Spain with 22 million customers and 41.58% of market share, where it also markets landline, broadband and pay television. Its principal competitor in Latin America is América Móvil. Source

 Telecom Italia Logo
TIM S.p.A., also operating under the name Telecom Italia, is an Italian telecommunications company with headquarters in Rome, Milan, and Naples, which provides telephony services, mobile services, and DSL data services. It is the largest Italian telecommunications services provider in revenues and subscribers. It was founded in 1994 by the merger of several state-owned telecommunications companies, the most prominent of which was Società Italiana per l’Esercizio Telefonico p.A., the former state monopoly telephone operator in Italy.
